It’s been on my “have to check that out”-list for a while because Kim Bodnia is in it and he was great in The Bridge. 

Has anyone else seen Killing Eve yet? If so, what did you think of it?

summary: QUESTION! What’s that killing eve stuff??? Looks rad as hell man!
question: QUESTION! What’s that killing eve stuff??? Looks rad as hell man!
answer: It’s great! So Eve (Played by Sandra Oh) is a desk bound M15 officer who starts linking together killings from across the world and pieces together that it’s a femal assassin. That female assassin is Villanelle (played by Jodie Comer) psychopath, love to hate her and hate to love her bamf, who soon finds out that Eve is tracking her. They both become obsessed with each other in a cat and mouse chase. But like both in a different way. Villanelle becomes romantically obsessed with Eve, and Eve becomes obsessed with taking her down. It’s a really nice show, very yandere, lots of action, pretty gorls, lovely cinematography and it has a lot of dark humor on the part of Villanelle. It’s a BBC show but it’s available on HULU

summary: I think about you all the time. I think about what you’re wearing and what you’re doing and who you’re doing it with. I think...
caption: I think about you all the time. I think about what you’re wearing and what you’re doing and who you’re doing it with. I think about what friends you have. I think about what you eat before you work, or what shampoo you use, what happened in your family. I think about your eyes and your mouth and what you feel when you kill someone. I think about what you have for breakfast. I just wanna know everything.
